Pension Fund Overview

As of March 31, 2017


Third largest pension fund in the United States
Estimated $192 billion in assets held in trust for pension benefits (final audited numbers available in Summer 2017)
Over 3,000 State and local government participating employers
More than one million members, retirees and beneficiaries
$10.9 billion paid out in benefits in fiscal year 2015-2016 
Two different systems: Employees' Retirement System (ERS) and Police and Fire Retirement System (PFRS)

Investments


As of March 31, 2016

Benefits Paid and Contributions

$10.91 billion in benefits paid
Employer contributions totaled $5.14 billion
State government contributions totaled $1.96 billion
Local government contributions totaled $3.18 billion
Employee contributions totaled $307 million

Member Information

Overall membership in the New York State & Local Retirement System (NYSLRS): 1,088,342
				   
647,399  employees (active and vested)
403,802 retirees; 37,141 beneficiaries


Average Pensions

Average pension for all ERS retirees in FY 2015: $22,415
Average pension for all PFRS retirees in FY 2015: $47,397
Economic Contributions of Retirees

$10.9 billion in benefits paid
$7.4 billion in spending
$10.4 billion in economic activity
$1.4 billion in property taxes 






