Investment Performance

The New York State Common Retirement Fund is the third largest public pension fund in the U.S., with an estimated $192 billion in assets under management (as of March 31, 2017).

As a long-term investor, the Fund has a robust diversification investment approach which capitalizes on market opportunities and weathers market ups and downs.

The Fund’s average five-year return is 10.17%, 10-year return is 7.12% and 20-year return is 8.69%.
Over the long-term, the Fund’s assumed rate of return to meet current and future retirement benefits is 7%.










