Company Overview of New York State Common Retirement Fund



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Vicki L. Fuller  Chief Investment Officer, New York State Common Retirement FundAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 1 Board Members in 1 different organizations across 2 different industries.See Board Relationships58--
Background

		Ms. Vicki L. Fuller has been the Chief Investment Officer at New York State Common Retirement Fund since August 30, 2012. Ms. Fuller served as the Senior Vice President and Director in the Institutional Marketing Public Funds Group at AllianceBernstein L.P. She has been a Senior Vice President of Alliance Capital Management Corporation since 1994 and is responsible for market and business development, product advocacy and client service for the Fixed Income Department's ... retail and private client business. She served as an Associate in the Corporate Finance department at Morgan Stanley and Co. from 1981 to 1983 and as a Rating Officer at Standard & Poor's Corporation from 1984 to 1985. She joined Equitable Capital Management Corporation in 1985 as a Senior Investment Manager, holding various positions including Managing Director from 1989 to 1993. She served as a Vice President of Alliance Capital Management Corporation from 1993 to 1994. She served as a Co-head of the Global High Yield Group at Alliance Capital. She joined Alliance Capital from Equitable Capital Management Corporation in 1993. Ms. Fuller serves as a Director at The Apollo Theater Foundation, Inc. She served as a Director at Long Island Lighting Co. Inc. since 1994. She served as a Member of Board of Directors at KeySpan Corporation. She is Chairperson of the KeySpan Foundation. She is a Member of the Board of Trustees of North Carolina Agricultural & Technology University. She is a Certified Public Accountant. She has a Bachelors degree from Roosevelt University and a Masters degree in Business Administration from the University of Chicago.Read Full Background




